		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=BellamDreamguard&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>/bow Jiggidyjay<br>/bow czaemon<br>/bow gbaji<br><br>Thank you for the direct, and well reasoned responses to my post.<br><br>I must admit, that the stuff that drops at the places I go isn't paticularly expensive stuff. I also have no way of knowing if I'm grouped with someone's main, or one of their alts. I have a bad habit of assuming that the people grouped with me are people's mains, and that the reason they don't have better stuff, is because they can't afford it.<br><br>Although I have probably err'd on the side of caution, I have made friends. Some of the folks who have gotten upgrades when grouped with me, have later proven worthy of the /friend and now are a far greater boon, than the lousy couple of K I could have recouped, if I had won a roll.<br><br>I honestly can't remember the last time I won a CAWU item - with the exception of LDoN augments, which are no drop anyway. What's funnier is, I can't remember the last time I even needed to roll on one. Until now, this hasn't bothered me. Deepwater gear is cheap, and Hill Giants are plentifull. Most of my eguipment is bought or quested for, and a lot of the level dependant attunables in the bazaar are really not bad. I've gotten some good deals. The quests leading up to DoN replaced some of my weaker slots.<br><br>Also, lately, I've been forming groups specifically to get someone something, and then recruiting based on who can benefit from drops. I camped the crystaline shardwurms, for a spell drop. Invited a zerker friend, but he had a ranger alt, so he had dibs on that drop. Invited a cleric friend, so he had dibs on that drop. - Anything else was up for random. Mutual self interest working to it's best advantage.<br><br>I still maintain, that the most important thing is to discuss the loot rules with each new member, regardless of what system you are using. If you do that, no one can get upset, as long as you adhere to the stated rules. I do plan to re-think my preference to CAWU in light of the valid points you have given.<br><br>Honestly, Czae, I would rather see gear be used than sold, but that is a personal preference. I'm probably too soft-hearted for my own good. You do bring up excellent points regarding the inequities of the CAWU system.<br><br>The everyone randoms on everything system really bothers me, though. One person could theoretically win 6 items that way, and the rest of the group walk away with nothing. Alot of the /random folks I've played with, do play that way - every item gets randomed.<br><br>Gbaji's system actually sounds pretty fair all around.<br><br>Maybe I'll switch to that - unless I'm grouped with friends, in which case, I don't see CAWU being a problem.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Bellam Dreamguard<br>Cavalier of Thunder<br>Qeynos Chapter<br>-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-<br> Cazic Thule <br><br><br>"LORD, WHAT CAN THE HARVEST HOPE FOR, IF NOT FOR THE CARE OF THE REAPER MAN?"<br><br> -Terry Pratchett</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Somewhere in the baryonic universe.</td></tr></table>
