		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Fri, Mar 4th 5:58 PM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=110832765395582215&num=73&page=2&post=1&replyto=1109977290248222211"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1109977290248222211></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=468881"><span id=Scholar>BellamDreamguard</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="100" width="71" src="/uf/BellamDreamguard/Velma.JPG"><br /><br />46 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.20]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=BellamDreamguard&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>I'm really curious about how to handle that exact situation, and what is considered the polite way to handle it. The way I've looked at it up til now, was on a situational basis. I'm friendly with a few individuals in a few different guilds. I've occasionally been invited to come along for XP grinds, and just recently, my first raid fell into this category.<br><br>The way I've looked at it up untill now, was that I expected a share of split proportionate to the role I played. When some people from VP helped me get my old sebilis key, I did not expect loot - they were all uber compared to me, and I was basically riding their coattails. As far as I was concerned, the key, and the XP was my reward. When I got invited along for a raid on Velketor, the experience of doing a raid was my reward. <br><br>But if I'm grinding with folks of about the same level, I think a plat split at the end of the night, without the items they set out to farm, isn't too much to ask. Honestly, even a token that says, &quot;Thank you, it was nice to have you along.&quot; is enough.<br><br>Usually, I can tell if I'm providing a positive contribution to a group, or not. If I am, then I deserve something. Even if it is just a token. Even a 20pp split says, &quot;Hey, we noticed you were here, and we appreciated it.&quot; But if I don't receive anything, then I don't make fuss over it. I'll just be less likely to come next time an invite gets sent out.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Bellam Dreamguard<br>Cavalier of Thunder<br>Qeynos Chapter<br>-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-~-<br> Cazic Thule <br><br><br>"LORD, WHAT CAN THE HARVEST HOPE FOR, IF NOT FOR THE CARE OF THE REAPER MAN?"<br><br> -Terry Pratchett</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Somewhere in the baryonic universe.</td></tr></table>
