		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.03]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=gbaji&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p><blockquote><b id="fs8">bushguide wrote:</b><hr size="1" />Thanks for the great post.&nbsp;&nbsp;I really needed to hear aout looting.  I have been playing since early Jan and did not know what was considered correct.  I have been in groups where things sat forever then when i looted with autosplit it says your share is 2pp.  I hate to think how much has gone into smoke because we did not loot.   I have also been in groups where players would not autosplit and would not answer group chat or tells asking them to put on autosplit.  I don't want to be greedy and have never played a caster.  I always offer a couple of times a session to give anything i get away.  the 1 in 6 thing helps a lot.<hr size="1" /></blockquote><br><br>Just to provide a bit more info (and since you probably don't know this).<br><br>Autosplit does *not* split money evenly. It does not make change out of whatever cash is on the mobs. What it does is divide each coin type by the number of characters in the group and give the remainder to the person looting. Depending on the mob level, it may generate a &quot;free&quot; 1cp, or 1sp/1cp split for every character if there were not enough coins to split of any type.<br><br>So. If you are in a group of 6 and loot a mob that has 5pp/5gp/5sp/5cp, you will get 5 of each coin type. Each of the other players will get either 1cp or 1sp/1cp (depending on level of mob, higher level will give a silver in addition to the copper).<br><br>The best method in an informal group is to just loot every X mobs, where X is the number of characters in the group. It need not be exact (because most people don't care that much about the cash loot on mobs). Alternatively, one person can always loot (with autosplit off) and then use the /split command to divvy up the coins at the end of the group period. The latter method is generally used for any instanced dungeons, but can certainly be used for normal camps as well.<br><br>Remember that monks really don't want extra weight, so having autosplit on will often just piss them off since over time, they'll just get loaded down with a bunch of silver and copper. At higher levels (heck even at lower levels), this stuff is pretty worthless. 100 silver equals one platinum, but weighs 100 times as much. No one's going to lug that stuff around for very long...</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
