		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=275512"><span id=Scholar>BatmanSixtySix</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />167 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.11]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=BatmanSixtySix&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Have to tbrow in my 2 CP here. <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/twocents.gif" /> <br><br>As a druid, in my 20s and 30s, I was perfectly happy letting others loot, with autosplit, while I regained mana for my healing/snaring/nuking details. I thought I received a fair share, until the first time I saw a corpse rotting and said, Heck, I have autosplit on, I will loot it. Up until that time, I thought all these guys were dropping was golds and silvers. WHAM, what do you mean they have 2 plats? <br><br>Then group conversation went something like this,<br><br>&quot;Wow, I got 2 plat off that? Is that what you have been getting?&quot;<br><br>&quot;Yeah, what did you get last time we split?&quot; <br><br>&quot;A gold and 2 silver&quot;<br><br>&quot;Dang, I only got 2 silver and a copper on that.&quot;<br><br>From then on, I would run up everyonce in while, to get some plat for me. According to most threads on Autosplit, the number of coins is evenly divided among the group members, with the remainder going to the ML. So, in a group of 6, if the loot is 17 plat, each will get 2 plat (12/6=2), with the other 5 remaining with the looter. A group of 5 would get 3 plat each (15/5=3), with the looter getting 2 plat. Either way, whoever loots makes out. <br><br>I have been a proponent of keeping track of plat with a ML system since, as long as you trust the ML. (Yeah, I am a Fox Mulder type on that, but that is another story.) The whole group will get more plat if it is devided at the end, as usually happens in LDON groups. Unfortunately, this does not work for pickup groups. The fairest way that I have seen so far works like this. <br><br>Group assigns each person a number as join group. Let each member be first looter on corpse, link any drops that are no drop, and request anything you want. Use /ran to determine any ties. Anything that is rotting for more that appx. 3 min is fair game for whoever wants. Use autosplit, but keep in mind that casters and priests won't get as much, so offer them any good drops. As group rotates people in and out, the new person is the lowest number, with group leader as number 1. Haven't been in too many groups that do it this way, but seems to work. <br><br></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

